Glampsite 1️⃣ @thehavenbin is done, ✅ and will be listed on Airbnb, Hipcamp and Vrbo on 4/24. 

Glampsite ✌🏾is in the works! 🏕️ 

— Fun Highlights

I come from a family of contractors. So, I don’t mind getting my hands dirty when needed in heels with a full beat. 🎨 😬 Ok, back to the project. LOL — I spray-painted these vinyl lattices black as skirting for the Cabin. (More on that will be on my YouTube soon) 

It wasn’t so much of an aesthetic choice but rather a temporary solution to hide the posts holding the #THOW. (Tiny Home on Wheels) I went with vinyl because we’re literally in the woods. The goal is to avoid terminates, carpenter bees and other wood destroyer insects. 
 
So much blood, sweat, tears, and 💸 have gone into this project, and we still have a ways to go with the development, 🚧 but this Tiny Haven nestled in the woods atop Lookout Mountain near the State Parks is a start to generating income to finance the rest of the projects and those shipping containers. #DontPlayWithIt LOL 

Follow @thehavenbin Tiny Cabin

None of what you see existed prior. We are nursing and safeguarding what’s left of the ecosystem and wildlife. More to come. This place is special. ESCÆPE! -

Here’s an update on my address sign from a few posts back at @thehavenbin. 

Owning land and a campground in a rural area presents its own set of challenges. One of the major hurdles is the expenses involved in hiring contractors, especially when it comes to work on the mountain. It can become quite costly.

Grateful to have a dad and uncle who are skilled contractors with expertise in home improvements and construction. I learned the business very early in life. So, I don’t mind getting my hands dirty every now and then, well, actually most of the time up here. LOL. I saved money by building and installing this modern address sign for our glamping/ STR guests to easily locate the property. Otherwise, I would have had to hire a contractor to handle the task @thehavenbin. I plan to help my contractors convert the campground into a micro-glamping (tiny home) community. Retreats coming soon! Xo. Oh, and yes the address is 420 😬

Link 🔗 in my bio to book your stay 🛖🌲 or https://www.airbnb.com/h/havenbin

#GlampGathering Memories ✨ Reflecting on an unforgettable glamping weekend as I planned and hosted the inaugural Pop-up Tent Girlfriends Weekend Getaway on my campground @thehavenbin. 🏕️

Eight women, most of whom had never met, with four who had never experienced camping or glamping before, united for a weekend of Yoga & Mindfulness Meditation, hiking to the waterfalls at Cloudland Canyon, cozy nights in tents, forest cooking adventures and themes, and the bond of sisterhood! Not one #CocaineBear on the Mountain insight. 🐻 LOL 

A special shoutout to my dear friend @iamronniesrose @selfhealersyoga for guiding us through enriching yoga sessions. 🧘🏿‍♀️Thanks to each of you for making this getaway special. Love you all! 🌻

Counting down the days until we gather again! I am excited to bring the girls along next spring through my nonprofit @girlpoweroutreach. 🌿
 
Proud #Campground & #LandOwner  #BlackOwnedBusiness and thrilled to be back home in ATL with my crew! 🌻

Host a Retreat at @thehavenbin 🏕️ Deets in my profile. Thank me later.

As we gear up for @thehavenbin’s inaugural winter glamping season above the clouds, it’s incredible to look back on the journey from the initial installation of power and the septic system to the heartfelt feedback from our guests. From creating the serene mellow wonder trail to planning future spring and summer camping initiatives for nonprofits and hosting retreats, it’s been an amazing transformation. I am grateful! 🏕️🌲❄️

I was super stoked when the lights finally came on, LOL! Developing raw land is definitely not an easy task.💡 my 3-2-1 was over it, so 1-2-3 was it. 🎬😂

🎥 Video recorded in Feb 2022 
📍 Rising Fawn, GA
